719955f-a.text:
Fulton Street, north aide, west from (No. 119) the head of Dutch (left) to Church Streets, and showing at the latter point the Vestry Office of Trinity Church. The 6-story structure under renovation. is the Raymond Building, No. 129 Fulton, 98-102 Nassau and 40 Ann Streets. This view shows it at the N.E. corner of Fulton and Nassau Streets. Opposing same is the 10-story Bennett Building, on the west side of Nassau,
north from Fulton to Ann Streets.
June 3, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
